title: City Health Dashboard
description: The goal of the City Health Dashboard is to provide communities and city leaders with an array of regularly updated data specific to neighborhood and/or city boundaries—such as life expectancy, park access, and children in poverty—to improve the health and well-being of everyone in the community. The database and interactive web tool enables exploration of the factors that shape health and the drivers of health equity at the city level.
display_note: Warning: Some of the measures included are modeled predictions at the small area level. Care should be take in interpretation at finer resolutions to ensure that variations in measures are due to change in measure of interest, and not due to the methodology generated to establish measure. Modeled data should be used with tremendous caution in analytical work.
